quran[12]{c,v,t,f}:
  26,121,"Indeed in that is a sign, but most of them were not to be believers."
  26,122,"And indeed, your Lord - He is the Exalted in Might, the Merciful."
  26,123,"ʿAad denied the messengers"
  28,67,"But as for one who had repented, believed, and done righteousness, it is expected [i.e., promised by Allāh] that he will be among the successful."
  28,68,"And your Lord creates what He wills and chooses; not for them was the choice. Exalted is Allāh and high above what they associate with Him."
  28,69,"And your Lord knows what their breasts conceal and what they declare."
  29,34,"Indeed, we will bring down on the people of this city punishment from the sky because they have been defiantly disobedient."
  29,35,"And We have certainly left of it a sign as clear evidence for a people who use reason."
  29,36,"And to Madyan [We sent] their brother Shuʿayb, and he said, "
  30,13,"And there will not be for them among their [alleged] partners any intercessors, and they will [then] be disbelievers in their partners."
  30,14,"And the Day the Hour appears - that Day they will become separated."
  30,15,"And as for those who had believed and done righteous deeds, they will be in a garden [of Paradise], delighted."